notesStmt.note: See Le Roux 1961, p.158 (in Jum and MSM - with 'nobis' for 'novus' - but not in insular sources)
In Fec-O, is lauds gosp for John: in Fec-B2 is sext for 6ta die post Nativ.

ant.aBody: Christus deus noster in quo divinitatis est plenitudo carnis nostrae infirma suscipiens novus natus est homo alleluia
